---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Privacy Policy - Clover"
  description="Clover's privacy policy for iOS and Android explaining how we collect, use, and protect your data."
>
  <Header />
  
  <main>
    <section class="py-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-pink-light/20 to-white">
      <div class="container-custom">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2">iOS and Android</p>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Effective Date: 1 December 2025</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
      <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Introduction</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
            Welcome to Clover ("we", "our", "us"). We are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use the Clover mobile application (the "App") on iOS and Android devices.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 mt-8">Information We Collect</h2>
          
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Location Data</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            When you grant permission, we collect your approximate location to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
            <li>Display your position on the map</li>
            <li>Show nearby baby changing facilities</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            We do not store, track, or share your location history. Location data is used only while you're actively using the App and is not transmitted to any servers for storage.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Photos</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            When you choose to add photos of baby changing places:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
            <li>Photos are uploaded to our database to help other users</li>
            <li>We do not extract or store any metadata (such as location tags, EXIF data) from your photos</li>
            <li>You control which photos you shareâ€”photo access is optional</li>
            <li>Photos are stored on our servers and displayed publicly within the App</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Camera Access</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            The App may request camera access to allow you to take photos of baby changing places directly within the App. Camera access is only used when you actively choose to take a photo and is not used for any other purpose.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Device Information</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            We may automatically collect certain information about your device, including:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
            <li>Device model and operating system version</li>
            <li>Unique device identifiers (for crash reporting only)</li>
            <li>App version</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            This information is used solely to improve app performance and fix bugs.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3 mt-6">Usage Data</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            We may collect anonymous usage data to improve the App, such as:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
            <li>App crashes and errors</li>
            <li>Feature usage statistics (which features are used most)</li>
            <li>Session duration</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            This data does not identify you personally and is aggregated for analytical purposes only.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 mt-8">How We Use Your Information</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            We use the information we collect to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li>Provide and improve the App's functionality</li>
            <li>Display baby changing places on the map</li>
            <li>Allow you to contribute photos to the community</li>
            <li>Fix bugs and improve performance</li>
            <li>Analyze usage patterns to enhance user experience</li>
            <li>Respond to user support requests</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 mt-8">Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR)</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            For users in the European Economic Area (EEA) and UK, we process your data based on:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li>Your consent (for location and photo access)</li>
            <li>Legitimate interests (for app functionality and improvements)</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 mt-8">Data Sharing</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties.
          </p>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            Photos you upload are shared publicly within the App to help other users find baby changing facilities.
          </p>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
            We may share anonymous, aggregated data with third parties for analytical purposes.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 mt-8">Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            The App may use third-party services that may collect information:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
            <li><strong>Map Providers:</strong> We use mapping services to display the map interface. These services may collect data according to their own privacy policies.</li>
            <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> We may use analytics services to understand app usage. These services collect anonymous usage data.</li>
            <li><strong>Cloud Storage:</strong> Photos are stored using cloud storage services, which have their own security and privacy measures.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
            These third-party services have their own privacy policies governing their use of data. We recommend reviewing their policies.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 mt-8">Data Retention</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li>Location data is not stored after you close the App</li>
            <li>Photos are stored indefinitely unless you request deletion</li>
            <li>Anonymous usage data is retained for analytical purposes</li>
            <li>Device crash logs are retained for up to 90 days</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 mt-8">Data Security</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            We use industry-standard security measures to protect your data, including:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
            <li>Encrypted data transmission (HTTPS/TLS)</li>
            <li>Secure server storage for photos</li>
            <li>Regular security audits</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
            However, no method of electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 mt-8">Your Rights</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            You have the right to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
            <li>Access the data we hold about you</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your data (including uploaded photos)</li>
            <li>Withdraw consent for location or photo access at any time through your device settings</li>
            <li>Object to processing of your data</li>
            <li>Request a copy of your data (data portability)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
            To exercise these rights, please contact us using the details below.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 mt-8">Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
            The App is designed for parents and caregivers. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 (or under 16 in the EEA). If you believe we have collected such information, please contact us immediately, and we will delete it.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 mt-8">International Data Transfers</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
            Your data may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your own. We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place to protect your data in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 mt-8">Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any material changes by:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li>Updating the "Effective Date" at the top of this page</li>
            <li>Providing an in-app notification (for significant changes)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
            We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 mt-8">Data Deletion Requests</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            To request deletion of your data:
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-neutral-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li>Contact us at the email below with "Data Deletion Request" in the subject line</li>
            <li>Include your device identifier (if known) or description of the photos you uploaded</li>
            <li>We will process your request within 30 days</li>
          </ol>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 mt-8">Google Play Data Safety</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            For Android users, please note:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-neutral-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li>Location data is not shared with third parties</li>
            <li>Photos are collected and shared publicly within the app</li>
            <li>No data is used for advertising or marketing purposes</li>
            <li>Data collection is optional (you can use the app without sharing location or photos for viewing purposes only)</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 mt-8">Contact Us</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, or to exercise your rights:
          </p>
          <div class="card p-6 bg-neutral-100 mb-6">
            <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-2">
              <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:alexpawlak+babymap@gmail.com" class="text-brand-pink hover:text-brand-pink-dark">alexpawlak+babymap@gmail.com</a>
            </p>
            <p class="text-neutral-700">
              <strong>For data protection inquiries (GDPR):</strong><br>
              <a href="mailto:alexpawlak+babymap@gmail.com" class="text-brand-pink hover:text-brand-pink-dark">alexpawlak+babymap@gmail.com</a>
            </p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 mt-8">Jurisdiction</h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
            This Privacy Policy is governed by the laws of the United Kingdom. For users in other jurisdictions, local data protection laws may also apply.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
